<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,794,1193,1345]" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1193,1217]" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is remarkable that both taxa 
<taxonomicName authorityName="-" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[661,794,1194,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giresunus">
<emphasis box="[661,794,1194,1217]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">H. giresunus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MORAWITZ" authorityYear="1872" box="[241,360,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis box="[241,360,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">H. glacialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are said to occur side by side in two provinces (
<collectingRegion box="[308,410,1257,1281]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[421,515,1257,1281]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Hakkâri</collectingRegion>
). Errors in older determinations cannot be completely ruled out here. To answer this question, females will have to be compared.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="297" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,793,1385,1505]" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,336,1385,1409]" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Distribution:</emphasis>
Has a disjunctive range in high mountain locations (
<quantity box="[364,515,1417,1441]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="297" unit="m" value="1800.0" valueMax="2100.0" valueMin="1500.0">1500–2100 m</quantity>
) of the Pyrenees, Alps, the Balkans and 
<collectingCountry box="[369,494,1449,1473]" name="Turkey" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[504,584,1449,1473]" name="Turkey" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Turkey</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[594,694,1450,1473]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[705,793,1449,1473]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Hakkâri</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[197,275,1481,1505]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[211,244,1429,1451]" captionTargetBox="[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetId="figure-259@68.[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 17: Distribution map of rarely recorded Hylaeus species in Turkey: species collected in only one (1-12) or two (II-X)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742935/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="297">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
